# Coveo Web Crawler — pokemondb.net Indexing

## Crawling rules (Admin → Source → Configuration → Crawling rules)

Individual Pokémon pages on pokemondb.net look like `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/bulbasaur` (exactly **one** path segment after `/pokedex/`). List/hub pages and game dexes use extra segments (e.g. `/pokedex/game/scarlet-violet`) or fixed slugs (`all`, `national`). Coveo applies rules to **full URLs**; see [Add a Web source — Crawling rules](https://docs.coveo.com/en/malf0160/index-content/add-a-web-source#crawling-rules-subtab).

### 1. Starting URLs

Set **Starting URL** to a Pokédex hub so discovery stays under `/pokedex/` and matches your inclusion rule:

- Recommended: `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/all` (links to every species page)

Avoid keeping only `https://pokemondb.net/` as the sole start URL if you use a **narrow inclusion** list — the homepage may not match your inclusion pattern and can be filtered incorrectly. If you keep the site root, add a second starting URL: `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/all`.

### 2. Inclusions

**Recommended for species-only indexing:** use a **regex** inclusion so only **one path segment** after `/pokedex/` matches (species slugs like `bulbasaur`). See **§4 Alternative: regex** below. That avoids indexing `…/pokedex/foo/moves/9`, `…/game/…`, etc., without maintaining a long exclusion list.

**Broader option (more exclusions needed):** Under **Inclusions**, select **Include non-excluded pages that match at least one rule**, then add:

| Rule type | Value |
|-----------|--------|
| **Matches wildcard rule** | `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/*` |

That keeps crawling under `/pokedex/` but **also** allows subpaths such as **`…/moves/…`** unless you exclude them explicitly (**`contains /moves/`** at minimum).

### 3. Exclusions (required)

Add **Exclusion** rules so list/game pages are not indexed as if they were Pokémon.

**Do not exclude your starting URL.** If **Starting URLs** includes `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/all`, you must **not** add an exclusion `is` → that same URL — Coveo will show **“Excluded starting URL(s) detected”** and the crawl cannot start correctly (unless you use advanced options like `ExpandBeforeFiltering`; simplest fix is to remove that exclusion). You may get **one** indexed hub document (`/pokedex/all`); filter it out in the query pipeline or UI if needed.

**Pokédex hubs (exact URLs — use “is”) — only if they are not used as a starting URL:**

- `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/national` (safe if your start URL is `/pokedex/all`)
- Omit `/pokedex/all` from exclusions when it is the starting address (see above)

**Multi-segment Pokédex sections (wildcard — “matches wildcard rule”):**

- `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/game/*`
- `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/stats/*` (if present / if you see these in Content Browser)

**Learnsets (required — easy to miss):** Pokémon move *learnset* pages use **`/moves/`** (plural), e.g. `…/pokedex/arctibax/moves/9`. A rule **`contains /move/`** matches the site’s **`/move/…`** encyclopedia URLs but **does not** match **`/moves/`**. Add **`contains /moves/`** (or wildcard `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/*/moves/*`) so those pages are excluded alongside other non-species paths.

**Other site areas** (species pages link to these; belt-and-suspenders **contains** rules work well):

| Rule type | String |
|-----------|--------|
| **Contains** | `/move/` |
| **Contains** | `/moves/` |
| **Contains** | `/type/` |
| **Contains** | `/ability/` |
| **Contains** | `/item/` |
| **Contains** | `/mechanic/` |
| **Contains** | `/pokebase/` |
| **Contains** | `/evolution/` |

After the first **rebuild/rescan**, open **Content Browser** and add exclusions for any remaining non-species URLs (e.g. other `/pokedex/...` hubs you see).

### 4. Alternative: regex (advanced)

One inclusion regex that matches only single-segment `/pokedex/{slug}` URLs (still add explicit exclusions for `all` and `national` if those slugs match):

`^https://pokemondb\.net/pokedex/[a-z0-9-]+$`

Test regex separately (e.g. [regex101](https://regex101.com/)) before saving.

---

**Tip**: Create a second **test** source with starting URL `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/bulbasaur` and the same inclusion/exclusion logic to iterate quickly without recrawling the full dex.

