## Web Scraping Configuration (JSON)

Attach to the source to extract custom metadata. Rules below are aligned with **current** species pages (verified against `/pokedex/cascoon` HTML, May 2026).

### Where the data lives on the page

| Field | On Cascoon’s HTML | Scraping note |
|-------|-------------------|---------------|
| **Type(s)** | First **Pokédex data** `table.vitals-table`: row **National №**, row **Type** with `a.type-icon` (e.g. Bug). | Do **not** use a global `td a.type-icon` rule — the **type defenses** grids also use `type-icon` and would poison facets. Scope to the **first** Pokédex vitals table + **Type** row. |
| **Generation** | There is **no** “Generation” row in that vitals table on Cascoon. Intro line: `… introduced in <abbr …>Generation 3</abbr>.` | A selector that only looks for `th` **Generation** in vitals will be **empty** on many Pokémon. Prefer the **intro** `<abbr>` after `<h1>` (see JSON). |
| **Picture** | `<meta property="og:image" content="https://img.pokemondb.net/artwork/large/cascoon.jpg">` and/or `a[rel="lightbox"][href*="artwork"]` around main artwork. | Old `infocard-lg` markup is **not** used on this layout — use **og:image** (if your crawler indexes `<head>`) or the **lightbox** artwork link. |
| **National №** | Same first **Pokédex data** `table.vitals-table` as Type: **first body row** is `<th>National №</th>` + `<td>` (often `<td><strong>1016</strong></td>`). | Map to **`pokemonnationalnumber`**. Row 1 = National, row 2 = Type (matches `pokemontype`’s `tr:nth-child(2)`). |

### Recommended scraping selectors (verified production set, May 2026)

Coveo's extractor is **jsoup-flavored CSS**, but jsoup pseudo-classes like `:has()` and `:matchesOwn()` have produced asymmetric failures in this project (see `docs/coveo-admin-playbook.md` "Selector style rejected"). **Stick to plain CSS3** — `:nth-of-type`, `:first-of-type`, attribute selectors, ID anchors, sibling combinators.

These selectors are entered in **Admin → Sources → _PokemonDB Crawl_ → Edit → Web Scraping → Metadata to extract**, one row per field.

```text
# Pokédex data (String / Multi-value)
pokemontype       main table.vitals-table:first-of-type tr:nth-child(2) td a.type-icon::text
pokemongeneration main > h1 ~ p:first-of-type abbr::text
pokemonability    main table.vitals-table:first-of-type td a[href^="/ability/"]::text
pictureuri        meta[property="og:image"]::attr(content)
pokemonnationalnumber main table.vitals-table:first-of-type tr:nth-child(1) td strong::text

# Base stats (Integer 32; #dex-stats anchor + tbody/tfoot positions)
pokemonhp       #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(1) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemonattack   #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(2) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemondefense  #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(3) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemonspatk    #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(4) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemonspdef    #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(5) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemonspeed    #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(6) td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
pokemonbst      #dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tfoot td.cell-num:first-of-type::text
```

**Selector design notes:**

- **`main table.vitals-table:first-of-type`** anchors to the **Pokédex data** table (the topmost vitals table), avoiding the Training / Breeding / Base Stats tables that share the class. Used for type / ability extraction.
- **National №** — `tr:nth-child(1)` is the first data row (National); value is in `td` (wraps `<strong>` on current pokemondb). If extraction is **empty** on tabbed species pages (forms in `.sv-tabs-panel`), try scoping the same row to the **active** panel: `main .sv-tabs-panel.active table.vitals-table:first-of-type tr:nth-child(1) td strong::text` (or `… td::text` if `<strong>` is absent).
- **`#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll`** anchors to the **Base Stats** wrapper specifically. `#dex-stats` is an empty anchor div whose ID is unique per HTML spec; `~ div.resp-scroll` finds the wrapper that holds the stats table (skipping the intervening `<h2>` heading).
- **`tbody tr:nth-of-type(N)`** for the six stats; **`tfoot`** for the Total row (Total lives in `<tfoot>`, separate from `<tbody>`).
- **`td.cell-num:first-of-type`** — the first numeric cell in a row is the actual stat. The two trailing `td.cell-num` cells are level-100 min/max projections, not the base stat.
- **Multi-form Pokémon** (Charizard, Mewtwo, Terapagos, …) render alternate-form stats under different headings; only the default form's table is preceded by `#dex-stats`, so we get the canonical value automatically.

**JSON form of the scraping config (`subItems` for completeness):**

```json
{
  "subItems": [
    {
      "type": "MetaData",
      "rules": [
        { "field": "pokemontype",       "selector": "main table.vitals-table:first-of-type tr:nth-child(2) td a.type-icon",      "attribute": "text"    },
        { "field": "pokemongeneration", "selector": "main > h1 ~ p:first-of-type abbr",                                            "attribute": "text"    },
        { "field": "pokemonability",    "selector": "main table.vitals-table:first-of-type td a[href^=\"/ability/\"]",            "attribute": "text"    },
        { "field": "pictureuri",        "selector": "meta[property=\"og:image\"]",                                                "attribute": "content" },
        { "field": "pokemonnationalnumber", "selector": "main table.vitals-table:first-of-type tr:nth-child(1) td strong",           "attribute": "text"    },
        { "field": "pokemonhp",         "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(1) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemonattack",     "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(2) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemondefense",    "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(3) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemonspatk",      "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(4) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemonspdef",      "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(5) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemonspeed",      "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tbody tr:nth-of-type(6) td.cell-num:first-of-type", "attribute": "text" },
        { "field": "pokemonbst",        "selector": "#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll tfoot td.cell-num:first-of-type",                  "attribute": "text" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

**If `pictureuri` is empty** (rare — connector skipping `<head>` meta tags), fall back to:

```json
{ "field": "pictureuri", "selector": "main a[rel=\"lightbox\"][href*=\"artwork\"]", "attribute": "href" }
```

> After saving scraping config: **rebuild** the Web source (not Refresh), then spot-check in Content Browser:
> - **Cascoon** (single-form, single-type)
> - **Golbat** (dual-type, multi-ability) — verify `pokemonhp + pokemonattack + pokemondefense + pokemonspatk + pokemonspdef + pokemonspeed == pokemonbst` (455 = 75+80+70+65+75+90)
> - **Charizard** (multi-form) — `pokemonbst` must be **534**, not 634 (Mega) or 634 (Gigantamax)
> - **Mewtwo** (multi-form) — `pokemonbst` must be **680**, not 780 (Mega)

