## Field Configuration (Admin Console → Content → Fields)

Create the following fields if they don't already exist:

| Field Name | Type | Multi-value | Facet | Sortable | Free text | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `pokemontype` | String | **Yes** | **Yes** | No | No | e.g. `Fire`, `Water` |
| `pokemongeneration` | String | No | **Yes** | No | No | e.g. `Generation 1` |
| `pokemonability` | String | **Yes** | **Yes** | No | No | e.g. `Inner Focus`, `Infiltrator` (semicolon-joined) |
| `pictureuri` | String | No | No | No | No | Full image URL |
| `pokemonnationalnumber` | String **or** Integer 32 | No | No | No | n/a | National Pokédex № (e.g. `150` or `0150`) — map from your Coveo scraper; see `web/src/lib/nationalDex.ts` |
| `pokemonbst` | **Integer 32** | No | **auto** | **auto** | n/a | Base Stat Total (Coveo auto-locks Facet+Sortable on Integer 32) |
| `pokemonhp` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | HP — unused by UI today; available for sort/ranking |
| `pokemonattack` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | Attack |
| `pokemondefense` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | Defense |
| `pokemonspatk` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | Special Attack |
| `pokemonspdef` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | Special Defense |
| `pokemonspeed` | Integer 32 | No | auto | auto | n/a | Speed |

**Integer 32 vs Long:** trial orgs offer Integer 32 only; non-trial orgs may also offer Long. For Pokémon stats (max ~720) Integer 32 is wildly sufficient and slightly more storage-efficient.

After adding fields, **rebuild the source** (full re-crawl, not Refresh) so values are indexed.

